Three suspected kidnappers have been arrested in Agbarho, Ughelli North Local Government Area of Delta State. Spokesperson of the Delta State Police Command, DSP Onome Onovwakpoyeya, who confirmed the arrest to NAN said the suspects were alleged to have been involved in the abduction of one Mr Emmanuel Piopio on Sunday on Ekwerhe Road, Agbarho. NAN gathered that the suspects were apprehended on Tuesday in Agbarho. “It is true that three suspected kidnappers have been arrested by the command. We are out for them; it is either the criminals repent or relocates out of Delta,” Onovwakpoyeya added that the suspects were arrested in Ophori-Agbarho community forest, with the help of the army and members of a vigilante group.